<img SRC = "http://www.xmission.com/~opafaf/NBsig1.jpg" BORDER=0 height=50 width=229><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/umarcys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marcys</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2/28/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12:57:34 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Brief rundowns on Rathe Calander/Rotation </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The Rathe calendar started out as.. &quot;Just posting intent&quot;<br>
<br>
Heh, one time a guild posted that they would be in fear over a two week time span ;p<br>
<br>
It worked relatively ok, when there were 3 guilds going fear.. then that number move to 5, 10 etc and so on.<br>
<br>
It still was a form of First Come First Serve. However, when someone's intent wasnt honored, there would be MASS DRAMA.  <br>
<br>
We had situation like, Server goes down.. 2 guilds/alliances log out in fear the night before patch, login when servers come up, so you have 30 people from each guild, which happened to be 2 of the biggest rivals, 60 total people in the plane of fear.  YOU KNOW something bad was gonna go down, when stuff popped.  Everyone was gonna claim they pulled first, and ks'd etc etc.  Fortunately the leaders on both sides talked something out and hammerd out a compromise.<br>
<br>
That incident was one of the turning points on the rathe, that reinforced adhering to a calendar.<br>
<br>
The Rathe Calendar is a compromise.  You agree to give up your freedom of &quot;first come first serve&quot;, in exchange for the right to post a day for fear/hate/sky. To have your Raid respected(not crashed/trained/ks by another guild/entity), hang out with your guild and have fun without stress, have control of how loot gets determined(In the high end game on the Rathe /random is very much despised)<br>
<br>
All this being said... Im indifferent about whether Eci will need a calendar.. when the server gets split, im sure there will be dialogue between the entities, and we'll all find a way to work things out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><table width="50%" border="0"> 
